latestPosts.caption: 8 months postpartum and slowly getting into my body’s new rhythm.I practised a gentler form of yoga while I was pregnant up until a day before I delivered Matara and continued to stay on the medicine ball in the hospital through early labour ( with approval from my doctor). The goal back then was to give my body all it needs in order to delivery naturally and thanks to all those Malasana’s,my doctor monitoring closely and support from my breath and body on the D-day.. I was able to push and be present with my breath taking me along. Now,the goal is to be able to take better care of my mind( which has obviously gone through a lot in the last few months )  and allow the body to heal through my practice. This is just one of the many reasons I swear by my yoga. I hope everyone finds a practice that takes them through this life and especially through this world we live in today. Have a great World Yoga Day! Practicing with @samikshashetty_ ❣️ #worldyogaday
